Problem 2.1

Note: Test for equality using code, not just visual inspection.

# basic solution
data    <- c(3, 5, 8, 15, 20, 21)
logdata <- log(data)
log(mean(data)) == mean(logdata)
[1] FALSE
# solution using dplyr
tibble(data = c(3, 5, 8, 15, 20, 21)) %>% 
  mutate(logdata = log(data)) %>% 
  summarize(xbar_data     = mean(data),
            xbar_logdata  = mean(logdata),
            log_xbar_data = log(xbar_data),
            test_equality = log_xbar_data == xbar_logdata)
# A tibble: 1 x 4
  xbar_data xbar_logdata log_xbar_data test_equality
      <dbl>        <dbl>         <dbl> <lgl>        
1        12         2.26          2.48 FALSE

Problem 2.2

Note: Test for equality using code, not just visual inspection.

data     <- c(1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 8, 11, 15)
sqrtdata <- sqrt(data)

# solution using dplyr
tibble(data = c(1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 8, 11, 15)) %>% 
  mutate(sqrtdata = sqrt(data)) %>% 
  summarize(xbar_data     = mean(data),
            med_data      = median(data),
            xbar_sqrtdata = mean(sqrtdata),
            med_sqrtdata  = median(sqrtdata))
# A tibble: 1 x 4
  xbar_data med_data xbar_sqrtdata med_sqrtdata
      <dbl>    <dbl>         <dbl>        <dbl>
1       6.5      5.5          2.39         2.34

Part (b)

# using base
table(Recidivism$Age25, Recidivism$Recid)
          
             No  Yes
  Under 25 1954 1123
  Over 25  9679 4263
prop.table(table(Recidivism$Age25, Recidivism$Recid), 1)
          
                  No       Yes
  Under 25 0.6350341 0.3649659
  Over 25  0.6942333 0.3057667
# using dplyr
Recidivism %>% 
  filter(complete.cases(Age25)) %>% 
  count(Recid, Age25)
# A tibble: 4 x 3
  Recid Age25        n
  <fct> <fct>    <int>
1 No    Under 25  1954
2 No    Over 25   9679
3 Yes   Under 25  1123
4 Yes   Over 25   4263
Recidivism %>% 
  filter(complete.cases(Age25)) %>% 
  group_by(Age25) %>% 
  summarize(prop_yes = mean(Recid == "Yes"))
# A tibble: 2 x 2
  Age25    prop_yes
  <fct>       <dbl>
1 Under 25    0.365
2 Over 25     0.306
